cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.CG

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with fiducial marker detection and pose estimation from a single image. It also involves image processing and pattern recognition techniques. 

It is also likely to belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as fiducial markers are commonly used in robot navigation and localization. 

The graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is also a possibility as augmented reality (AR) is mentioned as one of the applications of fiducial markers. 

Multimedia (cs.MM) is another possible sub-category as fiducial markers are used in multimedia applications such as video tracking and augmented reality. 

Finally, computer graphics (cs.CG) is a possible sub-category as the paper mentions flexible shape design and marker detection algorithm, which are related to computer graphics techniques.
